fluenced what he wrote and how he wrote it. Contributors further illuminate a print culture in the throes of transformation, providing useful fodder for historians of journalism and publishing in eighteenth- century Britain, while offering up rich new material for seasoned Boswell scholars.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aJames Boswell, Sutiman Papers, Broadside, The Hypochondriack, People of Scotland, The Death of An Amiable Young Lady, periodical writer, pamphlet writer, Boswell studies, Boswell’s periodical publication, Boswell’s ephemeral writing, print environment, press, publishing industry, print, print culture, periodical publishing, eighteenth-century Britain, broadsides, essays, journalism, literary career.1 aAston, Nigel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarnes, Celia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaudle, James J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaudle, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIngram, Allan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNewman, Donald J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNewman, Donald J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNewman, Donald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSeymour, Terry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTankard, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilson, Jennifer Preston, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilson, Jennifer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE CO